Key Match Events: The 76ers secured a commanding 123-94 victory over the Nets
Joel Embiid delivered a dominant performance with 28 points and 12 rebounds
The Nets opened the game with an 11-0 run but were unable to maintain the lead
Pre-Game Insights: The game was played without Ben Simmons, who missed due to left calf soreness
The 76ers will face the Phoenix Suns at home on Monday
Post-Match Reflections: The victory helped the 76ers jump to 14-19 on the season
Miscellaneous Highlights: Joel Embiid has the 6th most 25/10/5 games by a center in NBA history
The 76ers maintained their momentum to secure a commanding blowout victory
D'Angelo Russell contributed five points but exited the game with a right shin contusion
Others: Paul George supported Embiid with an impressive performance
Tyrese Maxey added to the effort with 18 points and seven assists
Caleb Martin took charge in the second quarter to help the 76ers extend their lead
